    "recap_url": "https://www.bgsufalcons.com/news/2026/3/15/baseball-falcons-come-up-short-in-high-scoring-sunday-rubber-match-against-miami-oh",
    "recap_headline": "Bowling Green State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OXFORD, Ohio\n\u2013\nThe Bowling Green State University baseball team finished out the weekend series against Miami (OH) on Sunday (March 15). The two teams battled back-and-forth, combining for a 20-run day. The RedHawks took the early lead, but the Falcons moved in front with a four-run top of the sixth. However, Miami battled back in the bottom half to reclaim the lead, eventually leading to the 13-7 final score in favor of the RedHawks. The game concluded BGSU's road trip to begin the season with the Falcons returning home on Tuesday (March 17) to host Findlay for a 3 p.m. first pitch.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nMiami (OH) tallied the first hit and run of the game in the first inning to take a 1-0 lead through one frame.\nThe Falcons broke into the scoring column in the third.\nCarter Mottice\nled off with a double and took third on a balk. A sacrifice fly off the bat of\nBrayden Curlis\nscored Mottice for a 1-1 tie.\nThe RedHawks reclaimed the lead in the bottom half with a two-run home run for a 3-1 score through three innings.\nTo begin the fourth,\nSam Seidel\nreached on an error and stole second. A single to center from\nTJ Takats\nwas enough to score Seidel, cutting the score down to 3-2.\nMiami again answered, scoring two in the bottom of the fourth to push their lead to 5-2.\nThe back-and-forth continued in the sixth. Takats drew a walk, setting up a two-run home run off the bat of\nAndrew DiLodovico\nto close the gap to 5-4.\nMottice drew a walk in the next at-bat to prompt a Miami pitching change.\nBrayden Curlis\nwelcomed the new arm with a two-run home run of his own to push the Falcons in front with a 6-5 lead.\nThe RedHawks again answered in the bottom of the sixth, moving back in front, 8-6. Miami added one in the seventh and four in the eighth for a 13-6 score.\nBowling Green answered in the ninth.\nGriffin Scheiderer\nwalked to put one on.\nAnthony Mitta\nstruck out, but a wild pitch resulted in him reaching with two outs.\nVinny Salvione\ncame through with a single to right, scoring Scheiderer for a 13-7 tally.\nSTAT LEADERS\nBrayden Curlis\n: 1-for-3, 1 HR, 3 RBI, 1 R\nCarter Mottice\n: 1-for-2, 1 2B, 2 R, 1 BB, 1 SB\nAndrew DiLodovico\n: 1-for-4, 1 HR, 2 RBI, 1 R\nGriffin Scheiderer\n: 1-for-4, 1 2B, 1 R, 1 BB\nTJ Takats\n: 1-for-4, 1 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nZack Horky\n: 1-for-4, 1 2B\nFALCON STAT FACTS\nVinny Salvione\ntallied a hit in the ninth inning, extending his hitting streak to a team-leading nine games.\nSam Seidel\nswiped a base for BGSU, giving him 44 stolen bases in his collegiate career. The mark ties him for eighth in program history, matching Glenn Honeycutt (1961-63).\nAndrew DiLodovico\nlaunched a home run in the sixth inning, the first of his collegiate career. DiLodovico tallied at least one hit and scored at least once in each game of the weekend series against Miami.\nGriffin Scheiderer\nextended his hitting streak to four games. During the four-game stretch, Scheiderer has five hits, three doubles, seven runs scored, one RBI and five walks drawn.\nSimilarly,\nCarter Mottice\nis now in the midst of a four-game hitting streak as well. During Mottice's stretch, he has four hits, four runs scored, two doubles, one RBI and three walks drawn.\nBrayden Curlis\nadded a season-high three RBI for the Falcons while matching his career-high, posting three RBI last year against Youngstown State on April 9.\nUP NEXT\nBowling Green will start the home slate of games for the season with their next five games at home. BGSU opens the home schedule with a 3 p.m. first pitch on Tuesday (March 17) against Findlay.\nAny schedule changes will be announced on BGSUFalcons.com as well as Twitter/X (@BGSU_Baseball).\nFollow the Falcons\nBe sure to follow the Falcons' baseball team on social media\nTwitter - @BGSU_Athletics and @BGSU_Baseball\nInstagram - 'bgfalcons' and 'bgsu_baseball'\nFacebook - 'BGSU Athletics'\nYouTube - 'Falcons Athletics'"
